                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/681: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-29T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 29, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>170. Your 308, July 26, 10 p.m. The American Government has not “promised to
                    appoint a financial expert.” The British Government informed us of the
                    appointment of Leith-Ross and asked that the American Government likewise
                    appoint a financial expert to be attached to the American diplomatic mission in
                    China. The Department replied that the American Government would give
                    consideration to the matter. As yet no decision has been reached.</p>
                <p>Please communicate the substance of the foregoing orally to Yen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
